Persuasion and Communication
- Authority and reciprocity (receiving something makes you obliged to provide something in return)
- Persuasion v Manipulation
    - whether the principles of influence naturally exist and are pointed to or manufactured counterfeits
- Bias 
    - a repeated, reproducible way in which the brain mistakes information as it absorbs and interprets it
- Fallacies
    - Errors in logic. Mistakes in argumentation and reasoning
- Debiasing techniques
    - the premortem: worst case, best case, most likely case of a project/initiative
    - intentionally slow down decision making process. slow is smooth, smooth is fast